- High-quality data refers to a data quality score above 90; 
- Validated data means the data has been confirmed to be accurate; 
- Electronic Health Records (EHR) are digital versions of a patient's chart.

- 'EHR System' refers to Electronic Health Record System, a digital version of a patient's chart; 
- 'Administrative' data type refers to non-clinical data related to the administration of healthcare services; 
- 'validated data' means that the data has been checked for accuracy and completeness.
